# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build outputs
dist/
build/
coverage/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Rust / cargo build outputs (matching-policy TEE contract).
# The `**/` prefix is required: the contracts live under
# `backend/contracts/...`, not at the repo root, so the bare
# `contracts/**/target/` pattern misses them.
**/contracts/**/target/
**/contracts/**/out/
**/contracts/**/cache/

# Foundry (forge) build outputs live next to the relayer
# source under backend/contracts/relayer/. The deployed ABIs
# are copied into `backend/src/services/settlement-rails/abi/`
# at build time and are the only forge artefacts that need
# to be tracked.
**/contracts/**/broadcast/
**/contracts/**/lib/

# `Cargo.lock` is intentionally tracked: the matching-policy
# contract is a `wasm32-wasip2` library that the TypeScript
# host consumes via `loadWasmComponent`, so a pinned
# `Cargo.lock` is the right reproducibility guarantee for
# the published artifact. The `**/` prefix matches the lock
# file at any depth (the contract lives under
# `backend/contracts/matching-policy/`).
!**/Cargo.lock

# Auto-generated runtime data. `backend/output/` holds the
# tenant identity (T3N signing key) that the backend mints on
# first boot, plus any future non-deterministic build output.
# The T3N SDK regenerates this directory on every fresh boot
# so it must NEVER be tracked — the file contains a private
# signing key (see `backend/output/identities/tenant_identity.json`).
**/output/

